Mayor of the DA-led Midvaal Municipality in Gauteng, Bongani Baloyi says he will leave no stone unturned in the dealing with the cash-for-jobs scandal involving two top executives in the municipality. Deputy Municipal Manager Thom Peeters was suspended after being fingered in irregular appointments by a whistle blower. Baloyi says a disciplinary hearing has since found him guilty. He says the council is also probing the Municipal Manager, Albert de Klerk’s alleged involvement. He was speaking at a media briefing in Johannesburg on the DA’s state of governance in municipalities. Listen below to Baloyi: <a href="https://iono.fm/e/729066">Content hosted by iono.fm</a>